.TH "port_cfg" 9 "port_cfg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
port_cfg \- set port register bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" port_cfg
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "int port "  ","
.BI "int offset "  ","
.BI "u16 bits "  ","
.BI "int set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "port" 12
The port index.
.IP "offset" 12
The offset of the port register.
.IP "bits" 12
The data bits to set.
.IP "set" 12
The flag indicating whether the bits are to be set or not.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine sets or resets the specified bits of the port register.
